-- Econet Wireless Zimbabwe Full-Year Profit Rises 18%
-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 2012-04-24T14:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/econet-wireless-zimbabwe-full-year-profit-rises-18-1-.html
Econet Wireless Zimbabwe Ltd. (ECWH) , the
country’s biggest mobile-phone carrier, said profit for the
fiscal year through February rose 18 percent to $165.7 million.  Revenue climbed 24 percent to $611 million with subscribers
up 16 percent to 6.4 million, Douglas Mboweni, chief executive
officer of the Harare-based company, told analysts today at a
briefing in the city.  Econet invested $614 million over the past three years in
network infrastructure, Krison Chirairo, the company’s financial
director, said at the briefing.  Total assets increased 27 percent to $812.4 million, he
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
